Thank you for your services always!

I have been a customer for five years, during which time I was dedicated to the company and recommended their services to several of my clients and friends. This year, I was charged a service fee before the service was performed. When I called to inquire about the charge, I discovered that no one had contacted me to schedule a service date. We arranged a date during that call.

However, about two weeks later, I received a call informing me that they couldn't perform the service unless I paid an additional amount of money, which was a 59% increase. I expressed that charging customers before the service is performed is inappropriate. The customer service representative was rude, and when I requested a refund, I was told that refunds are not typically provided but that she would speak to her supervisor.

This experience was unprofessional and not the way to conduct business. Consequently, I have canceled my membership and am now waiting for my refund.

reviews.text: "Pressure Cleaning Orlando" is above and beyond our expectations! Garrett the owner and his well trained crew surely knew their business.They arrived on schedule, gave us there plan and started working right away removing several years of well water rust and grime..They pressure washed, all of our pavers, added new sand and sealed all pavers..They made sure all funiture was out of the way and placed it back exactly! reviews.text: Rudy did phenomenal! We can't believe how much of a transformation we are seeing. Rudy pressure washed our front and backyard's pathways, drive way, porch and its ceiling, all exterior walls and windows, and parts of the roof. It's like night and day, we didn't even know the color of the backyard pathway until he worked his magic. He did a THOROUGH job and was great with explaining everything through. Never received this high quality of service before, so happy we found Liam Pressure Cleaning. Wont go anywhere else ever again. Thank you!
Rudy did a fantastic job on my house. He pressure washed my driveway, patio, vestibule, and the exterior. My house is noticeably brighter. His work is efficient, good timing, and reasonably priced.

Where to begin!! Rudy did our backyard pool pavers and our driveway. We have a pretty decent size backyard. It was NIGHT & DAY. His professionalism was outstanding and his work speaks for itself. I will be recommending him to anyone that asks! Thank you Rudy!!

This guy is simply amazing!!!!  Rudy pressure washed out sidewalks and they are sparkling!!  His kindness and professionalism shone through!!! If you are looking for a honest and hardworking man, he is your best choice!

I will tell you that Rudy will have a fleet of trucks one day! He is a young man focused on his business and your satisfaction! I have run operations at a VP level for some large restaurant chains and we called employees like Rudy Hypo's meaning High Potential, someone that will go somewhere and he is one of them.  I asked him to come over after the job I saw him do for my neighbor and quote to wash my roof of my enclosed room over next to the pool. He did an amazing job but time  And the Florida Sun had taken its toll on the roof and the paint had dried to almost a powder leaving just bare aluminium. I said to him well I guess I need to get coated and he said he had experience painting and I asked him if it was something that he would do He said yes that he felt comfortable his experience in painting was good and he would be able to do the job. He gave me a very fair quote showed up on time and he did an amazing job!  I would recommend him for any job that you have is he is not the type of person that will say he can do something and then try to figure it out hes very honest and works very hard you will be very pleased with anything that he does for you! The pictures are the after he cleaned the roof which was all black mold, dirt and flaking paint... As you can see in the after pictures he did a great job painting it and the sealer paint for that job is very tricky because it's thick and has to be applied evenly and thick and he did a great job as you can see!
